without drinking.

849
00:55:54,562 --> 00:55:56,606
Why? Did something happen?

850
00:55:57,231 --> 00:55:59,067
You know what an incentive trip is, right?

851
00:55:59,150 --> 00:56:01,611
We reached our goal
after working our butts off for a month.

852
00:56:02,487 --> 00:56:04,489
But they sent us on a day trip to Bali.

853
00:56:04,572 --> 00:56:06,366
A day trip to Bali?

854
00:56:06,449 --> 00:56:07,408
Yes.

855
00:56:07,492 --> 00:56:08,743
I just got back.

856
00:56:22,632 --> 00:56:23,966
Hey!

857
00:56:24,050 --> 00:56:25,968
You ruined my hair.

858
00:56:26,552 --> 00:56:28,596
Good grief.

859
00:56:28,679 --> 00:56:29,597
I'm sorry.

860
00:56:29,680 --> 00:56:31,099
Do you want to check these?

861
00:56:34,894 --> 00:56:36,562
There's nothing special about Bali.

862
00:56:37,063 --> 00:56:40,191
With a beach and a palm tree,
we're basically there.

863
00:56:40,817 --> 00:56:43,694
YOU BETTER BALI-VE IT

864
00:56:43,778 --> 00:56:46,030
So you're saying we can't go?

865
00:56:46,114 --> 00:56:47,323
Yes, that's right.

866
00:56:47,407 --> 00:56:49,158
This time, we can settle for this.

867
00:56:49,242 --> 00:56:50,701
We'll go to Thailand next time.

868
00:56:50,785 --> 00:56:54,664
You said we'd go to Southeast Asia
if we reached 30%.

869
00:56:54,747 --> 00:56:58,626
We worked our butts off
without any bathroom breaks.

870
00:56:58,709 --> 00:56:59,794
Tell me about it.

871
00:56:59,877 --> 00:57:04,048
Next time, I'll do whatever it takes
to get you girls a trip to Thailand.

872
00:57:04,132 --> 00:57:06,175
So let's increase the sales a little more.

873
00:57:06,259 --> 00:57:07,385
Ms. Do.

874
00:57:07,468 --> 00:57:09,387
We came somewhere nice.

875
00:57:09,470 --> 00:57:12,306
Don't ruin the mood.
Let's talk about good things only.

876
00:57:12,890 --> 00:57:15,810
I've been to Bali before.
It's identical to this place.

877
00:57:16,519 --> 00:57:18,521
It's a waste of time to fly there!

878
00:57:19,063 --> 00:57:19,897
Hey.

879
00:57:21,107 --> 00:57:22,024
The special effects.

880
00:57:24,902 --> 00:57:26,028
Is this good?

881
00:57:26,112 --> 00:57:28,030
- Yes.
- Keep smiling.

882
00:57:28,114 --> 00:57:29,949
Nice. Wonderful.

883
00:57:30,032 --> 00:57:31,117
- You look like Lee Hyo-ri.
- Me?

884
00:57:31,200 --> 00:57:32,535
<i>That's the worst.</i>

885
00:57:32,618 --> 00:57:33,953
She's so evil.

886
00:57:34,579 --> 00:57:36,456
She's just like my supervisor.

887
00:57:36,539 --> 00:57:37,915
What did your supervisor do?

888
00:57:38,624 --> 00:57:40,877
She promised to make Pyeong-hwa a purser

889
00:57:40,960 --> 00:57:43,045
if she increased sales,
so she made her team first.

890
00:57:43,129 --> 00:57:45,173
But instead,
she promoted Pyeong-hwa's junior,

891
00:57:45,256 --> 00:57:46,507
her favorite.

892
00:57:46,591 --> 00:57:50,261
She wouldn't have worked to the point of
hurting her back had she known.

893
00:57:50,344 --> 00:57:53,598
Are in-flight sales
that important for becoming a purser?

894
00:57:53,681 --> 00:57:57,101
They bring in a lot of money
thanks to their high profit margin.

895
00:57:57,602 --> 00:57:59,479
The company keeps pushing us.

896
00:57:59,562 --> 00:58:01,689
If your team doesn't reach
its monthly sales target,

897
00:58:01,773 --> 00:58:02,982
you'll get a poor performance rating.

898
00:58:03,065 --> 00:58:05,610
Are there any incentives
for selling a lot?

899
00:58:05,693 --> 00:58:07,195
No, there aren't.

900
00:58:07,278 --> 00:58:08,780
If I do well, it's a given.

901
00:58:08,863 --> 00:58:10,907
If I do poorly,
I get on my superiors' bad side.

902
00:58:11,991 --> 00:58:13,868
What do you expect from King Group?

903
00:58:13,951 --> 00:58:16,954
Even Sa-rang was chosen
as the best talent for two years straight,

904
00:58:17,038 --> 00:58:19,081
but all she was given was
a smiley face badge.

905
00:58:19,874 --> 00:58:21,083
Hold on.

906
00:58:21,876 --> 00:58:25,421
You were chosen as the best talent
for two consecutive years,

907
00:58:25,505 --> 00:58:26,756
but all you got was a badge?

908
00:58:27,632 --> 00:58:29,675
Since it was two years, I got two badges.

909
00:58:30,510 --> 00:58:32,428
I wasn't expecting anything, so it's okay.

910
00:58:32,512 --> 00:58:35,097
It's not okay.
You always say that with everything.

911
00:58:35,181 --> 00:58:37,350
What can I do if it's not okay?

912
00:58:41,646 --> 00:58:43,481
So the best talent only got a badge.

913
00:58:44,065 --> 00:58:46,526
Da-eul, even after reaching your goal,

914
00:58:46,609 --> 00:58:48,611
you weren't given the trip
you were promised.

915
00:58:48,694 --> 00:58:52,907
Pyeong-hwa, you were promised a promotion
if your team came in first,

916
00:58:52,990 --> 00:58:54,283
but someone else got it.

917
00:58:55,618 --> 00:58:57,203
It's my fault for being so naive.

918
00:58:58,079 --> 00:58:59,539
Why in the world…

919
00:58:59,622 --> 00:59:02,041
The company should recognize
and reward its employees.

920
00:59:02,124 --> 00:59:04,085
Also, a superior not keeping their word?

921
00:59:04,168 --> 00:59:07,797
How does it make sense
for a superior to break their promise?

922
00:59:07,880 --> 00:59:08,756
It does.

923
00:59:08,840 --> 00:59:11,259
The higher-ups only look up.

924
00:59:11,342 --> 00:59:13,177
They don't care about us.

925
00:59:13,261 --> 00:59:16,430
If things go well, it's thanks to them.
If not, it's our fault.

926
00:59:16,514 --> 00:59:18,224
Why is that your fault?

927
00:59:18,808 --> 00:59:20,852
All three of you are not at fault.

928
00:59:20,935 --> 00:59:22,353
The fault lies in the company

929
00:59:22,436 --> 00:59:24,105
and your superiors for tricking you.

930
00:59:24,814 --> 00:59:27,733
We cannot let this slide.

931
00:59:28,317 --> 00:59:33,114
I'll do whatever it takes
and take responsibility to amend this.

932
00:59:34,240 --> 00:59:36,284
- Wait.
- Won't it be difficult for you

933
00:59:36,367 --> 00:59:37,493
to do much as a manager?

934
00:59:38,327 --> 00:59:39,412
I know, right?

935
00:59:39,495 --> 00:59:40,997
If he were a department manager…

936
00:59:41,080 --> 00:59:42,331
That's hard too.

937
00:59:42,415 --> 00:59:43,916
He needs to be a head manager at least.

938
00:59:44,000 --> 00:59:46,335
Hey, didn't you hear what Sa-rang said?

939
00:59:46,419 --> 00:59:49,589
She said her head manager
was a total jerk.

940
00:59:49,672 --> 00:59:51,215
He goes to work for fun.

941
00:59:51,299 --> 00:59:53,593
He wouldn't care about us lowlings.

942
00:59:54,343 --> 00:59:55,720
Right, Sa-rang?

943
01:00:02,143 --> 01:00:03,060
No.

944
01:00:04,395 --> 01:00:07,398
No. He's not a jerk anymore.

945
01:00:07,481 --> 01:00:08,983
He's a really nice person.

946
01:00:09,066 --> 01:00:11,027
Hey, get your head straight.

947
01:00:11,110 --> 01:00:12,778
As is the king, so are the subjects.

948
01:00:12,862 --> 01:00:15,406
If he were a good person,
we wouldn't be suffering like this.

949
01:00:15,489 --> 01:00:16,490
Right, Mr. No?

950
01:00:17,158 --> 01:00:18,451
I think he's all right.

951
01:00:18,534 --> 01:00:20,786
Someone like Mr. No
should be the head manager.

952
01:00:20,870 --> 01:00:21,913
You're right.

953
01:00:21,996 --> 01:00:25,499
Okay. May Mr. No become the head manager!

954
01:00:28,419 --> 01:00:30,838
It doesn't matter who does it.

955
01:00:30,922 --> 01:00:32,673
If you work this hard for the company,

956
01:00:32,757 --> 01:00:34,675
the company should also treat you well.

957
01:00:34,759 --> 01:00:36,802
I don't even expect that much.

958
01:00:36,886 --> 01:00:39,680
I just want to be appreciated
for the work that I do.

959
01:00:40,514 --> 01:00:43,601
Why do we have to wish for something
that should already be given?

960
01:00:44,185 --> 01:00:46,687
We deserve what we deserve.

961
01:00:53,069 --> 01:00:55,947
Anyway, it is an honor.

962
01:00:56,030 --> 01:00:58,699
The best employee at King Air,
King Distribution,

963
01:00:58,783 --> 01:01:00,409
and King Hotel.

964
01:01:00,493 --> 01:01:03,663
I'm with the best employees
of King Group right now.

965
01:01:04,622 --> 01:01:05,706
Like I said,

966
01:01:05,790 --> 01:01:08,250
you should be the head manager, Mr. No.

967
01:01:08,334 --> 01:01:10,461
If you run for the position,
I'll vote for you.

968
01:01:10,544 --> 01:01:12,338
It's Mr. No.

969
01:01:12,421 --> 01:01:13,965
- It's Mr. No.
